<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="86.[670,1199,654,1763]" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">
IDENTIFICATION: Descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[799,1070,919,942]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Phyllostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[799,1070,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">Phyllostomus hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have appeared in many publications; we consulted those in 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, G. G. &amp; A. M. Greenhall" box="[792,1193,977,1000]" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist." pageId="86" pageNumber="86" pagination="191 - 301" part="122" refId="ref94360" refString="Goodwin, G. G., and A. M. Greenhall 1961. A review of the bats of Trinidad and Tobago: descriptions, rabies infection, and ecology. Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist. 122: 191 - 301." title="A review of the bats of Trinidad and Tobago: descriptions, rabies infection, and ecology" type="journal article" year="1961">Goodwin and Greenhall (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[670,859,1006,1029]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), 
<bibRefCitation author="Taddei, V. A." box="[988,1193,1006,1029]" journalOrPublisher="Ciencia e Cultura" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" pagination="621 - 632" part="27" refId="ref100692" refString="Taddei, V. A. 1975 a. Phyllostomidae (Chiroptera) do norteocidental do Estado de Sao Paulo. I. Phyllostominae. Ciencia e Cultura 27: 621 - 632." title="Phyllostomidae (Chiroptera) do norteocidental do Estado de Sao Paulo. I. Phyllostominae" type="journal article" year="1975">Taddei (1975a)</bibRefCitation>
, Swanepoel and 
<bibRefCitation author="Genoways, H. H. &amp; S. L. Williams" box="[872,1091,1036,1059]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="86" pageNumber="86" pagination="323 - 335" part="48" refId="ref93773" refString="Genoways, H. H., and S. L. Williams 1979. Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 48: 323 - 335." title="Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1979">Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, and Anderson (1997). Two subspecies of are currently recognized: 
<emphasis box="[818,836,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[856,871,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">h</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[890,1027,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">panamensis</emphasis>
(Honduras to Peru and east to Venezuela) and 
<emphasis box="[1077,1095,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1114,1129,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">h</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Phyllostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(eastern Venezuela south to northern Bolivia and southeastern Brazil) (Koopman, 1994). These are distinguished principally on the basis of size, with 
<emphasis box="[953,971,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[990,1005,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">h</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[1024,1121,1271,1294]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Phyllostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[1024,1121,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being the smaller form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[670,1199,654,1763]" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">
Our voucher material conforms closely with previous descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authority="hastatus" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Phyllostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hastatus" subSpecies="hastatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="86">Phyllostomus hastatus hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with measurements generally falling within the range of variation previously reported from the Guianas. One exception is a particularly small adult male (AMNH 267907), some measurements of which are less than any previously reported for the species (e.g., forearm length of 77.5 mm, compared with 79.0 mm for the smallest male reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Taddei, V. A." box="[887,1071,1622,1645]" journalOrPublisher="Ciencia e Cultura" pageId="86" pageNumber="86" pagination="621 - 632" part="27" refId="ref100692" refString="Taddei, V. A. 1975 a. Phyllostomidae (Chiroptera) do norteocidental do Estado de Sao Paulo. I. Phyllostominae. Ciencia e Cultura 27: 621 - 632." title="Phyllostomidae (Chiroptera) do norteocidental do Estado de Sao Paulo. I. Phyllostominae" type="journal article" year="1975">Taddei [1975a]</bibRefCitation>
). Comparisons of this diminutive individual with other specimens in our sample, however, failed to reveal any morphological differences other than size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
