<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[128,657,214,648]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: We recorded 56 captures (possibly including some recaptures) of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[128,392,273,296]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Phyllostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[128,392,273,296]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Phyllostomus hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which 34 were in groundÂ­level mistnets and 22 were in elevatÂ­ ed mistnets. The 34 groundÂ­level captures included 9 in wellÂ­drained primary forest, 11 in swampy primary forest, 6 in creekside primary forest, and 8 in manmade clearings (7 were taken in a banana/cacao plantation on a single night). Of the 22 elevated mistnet captures, 17 were in nets suspended 10â23 m above a narrow dirt road, 4 were made at 20â38 m above a treefall gap in wellÂ­drained primary forest, and 1 was at 7â10 m above a treefall in creekside primary forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
